From: User-3090 <71881005+User-3090@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 08:04:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/8] feat: follow host appearance for unconfigured themes

Treat an omitted auto_switch value differently from an explicit false. A fully
unconfigured theme now follows the host with catppuccin for dark appearance and
one-light for light appearance, while explicit themes retain manual behavior
and users can opt out with auto_switch = false.

Update the sample configuration, unreleased documentation, localized guidance,
and configuration reference to describe the new default.

