 dark_name = "catppuccin"
 ```
 
-`auto_switch` defaults to `false`, so existing theme configs keep manual behavior. If `light_name` or `dark_name` is omitted, Herdr uses the matching built-in sibling for the configured `name` when one exists, such as `tokyo-night`/`tokyo-night-day` or `gruvbox`/`gruvbox-light`. Manual theme selection in Settings disables `auto_switch`.
+When no theme fields are configured, Herdr follows the host appearance automatically. Set `auto_switch = false` to opt out, or set it to `true` to enable switching alongside explicit theme settings. If `light_name` or `dark_name` is omitted, Herdr uses the matching built-in sibling for the configured `name` when one exists, such as `tokyo-night`/`tokyo-night-day` or `gruvbox`/`gruvbox-light`. Manual theme selection in Settings disables `auto_switch`.
 
 You can override individual colors:
 
